summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from F. C. West and Ellen Ruth West, his wife, to the City of Georgetown (now The City of Seattle), dated April 11th, A. D. 1910, to the following described real estate: Beginning at Northeast corner of The L. M. Collins Donation Claim No. 46; thence south Thirty (30) feet; thence west Two Hundred and Twenty and .59 feet (220.59); thence north Thirty (30) feet to the north line of said and D. C.; thence east of said north line to place of beginning; situated in the County of King, State of Washington, to be used for street purposes only.
